# General Counsel of the Department of the Air Force

The **General Counsel of the Department of the Air Force** (acronym **SAF/GC**) is the chief legal officer of the [United States Department of the Air Force](/United_States_Department_of_the_Air_Force). This position is responsible for providing legal advice to the [Secretary of the Air Force](/United_States_Secretary_of_the_Air_Force), the [Under Secretary of the Air Force](/United_States_Under_Secretary_of_the_Air_Force), and other senior leaders within the department. The General Counsel also serves as the chief ethics official for the Department of the Air Force.

## Overview

The General Counsel of the Department of the Air Force is appointed from civilian life by the [President of the United States](/President_of_the_United_States) with the advice and consent of the [United States Senate](/United_States_Senate). The role is governed by [10 U.S.C. § 9019](/Title_10_of_the_United_States_Code), which outlines the duties and responsibilities of the position.

According to Secretary of the Air Force Order No. 111.5, dated July 14, 2005, the General Counsel is the chief legal officer and chief ethics official of the Department of the Air Force. Legal opinions issued by the Office of the General Counsel are the controlling opinions of the Department of the Air Force. The General Counsel provides advice in accordance with applicable statutes on any legal subject and on other matters as directed by the Secretary.

## Duties and Responsibilities

The General Counsel advises the Secretary of the Air Force, the Under Secretary of the Air Force, and the Assistant Secretaries of the Air Force, as well as the [Chief of Staff of the Air Force](/Chief_of_Staff_of_the_United_States_Air_Force), the [Chief of Space Operations](/Chief_of_Space_Operations), and other military leaders of the [United States Air Force](/United_States_Air_Force) and the [United States Space Force](/United_States_Space_Force) on legal matters. However, the General Counsel does not handle statutory duties under the [Uniform Code of Military Justice](/Uniform_Code_of_Military_Justice), which are performed by the [Judge Advocate General of the Air Force](/United_States_Air_Force_Judge_Advocate_General%27s_Corps).

